2. cs.ST (Statistics): The paper deals with the problem of estimating a risk measure from data, which is a statistical problem. Hence, cs.ST is also a likely sub-category. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The proposed method involves numerical integration, which is a topic in numerical analysis. Hence, cs.NA is also a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers a vehicular traffic routing application, which involves control and optimization of systems. Hence, cs.SY is also a likely sub-category. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The vehicular traffic routing application involves multiple agents (vehicles), and hence, cs.MA is also a possible sub-category.
